By your argument, all marriage would not fit the Categorical Imperative qualifications, so all marriage must be made illegal. Categorical ImperativeQuoting from wikipedia here: "From this step, Kant concludes that a moral proposition that is true must be one that is not tied to any particular conditions, including the identity of the person making the moral deliberation. A moral maxim must have universality, which is to say that it must be disconnected from the particular physical details surrounding the proposition, and could be applied to any rational being. "